details.root_cause: Filter object recreation causing infinite useCallback dependency trigger
fixes_applied: Memoized filter objects in AllProjectsDashboard using useMemo
Broke circular dependency chains with useRef for stable function references
Separated WebSocket lifecycle from filter changes using split useEffect
Eliminated duplicate API calls on component mount
Fixed infinite loop from filter object recreation on every render

technical_details.primary_issue: Filter object literal recreated on every render in AllProjectsDashboard.tsx:59-66
secondary_issues: WebSocket restart on every filter change
Mixed cleanup concerns in single useEffect

fixes_implemented.filter_memoization: Added useMemo for stable filter object references
fixes_implemented.circular_dependency: Used fetchProjectsRef.current for stable polling callbacks
fixes_implemented.websocket_lifecycle: Split data fetching and connection management useEffects
fixes_implemented.duplicate_calls: Removed redundant fetchProjects call from mount effect

performance_impact.before: Infinite re-renders, memory leaks, excessive API calls
performance_impact.after: Stable renders, proper cleanup, 30-second polling intervals only
performance_impact.memory_usage: Reduced by eliminating infinite render loops
performance_impact.api_calls: Reduced to proper intervals (30s) instead of continuous

runtime_context.testing_status: hooks compile correctly, dev server runs without recursion errors

next_steps: Validate real-time WebSocket functionality in production
